## React Performance

### No `useMemo` / `useCallback`

React Compiler (Babel plugin) handles memoization in production. Do not add manually.

```typescript
// ❌ — redundant, adds overhead
const memoized = useMemo(() => expensiveComputation(a, b), [a, b]);
const handler = useCallback(() => onChange(value), [value]);

// ✅ — let the compiler handle it
const memoized = expensiveComputation(a, b);
const handler = () => onChange(value);
```

### Avoid `useEffect` for data fetching

```typescript
// ❌ — dual firing, no cleanup, no SSR support
useEffect(() => {
  fetch('/api/jobs').then(res => res.json()).then(setJobs);
}, []);
```

Use React Query hooks instead:
```typescript
// ✅ — SSR prefetch, caching, deduping, background refetch
const { data: jobs } = useJobsQuery();
```

### Avoid `useEffect` for derived state

```typescript
// ❌
const [fullName, setFullName] = useState('');
useEffect(() => {
  setFullName(`${firstName} ${lastName}`);
}, [firstName, lastName]);

// ✅ — derive at render time
const fullName = `${firstName} ${lastName}`;
```

### Avoid side effects in render

```typescript
// ❌ — side effect in render body
function Component() {
  const router = useRouter();
  if (!auth) router.push('/login'); // redirect in render = anti-pattern
  return <div />;
}

// ✅ — guard at top, no side effect
function Component() {
  const router = useRouter();
  if (!auth) {
    router.push('/login');
    return null;
  }
  return <div />;
}
```

### Stable object/array references in JSX

```typescript
// ❌ — new object on every render, causes child re-render
return <Table columns={[{ key: 'id', label: 'ID' }]} />;

// ✅ — define outside component or memoize
const COLUMNS = [{ key: 'id', label: 'ID' }] as const;
return <Table columns={COLUMNS} />;
```

### Heavy list rendering

```typescript
// ✅ Always provide stable `key`
return items.map(item => <ListItem key={item.id} {...item} />);

// ❌ key={index} breaks animations and state in lists
return items.map((item, i) => <ListItem key={i} {...item} />);
```

### Image optimization

```typescript
// ✅ Use next/image for all user-visible images
import Image from 'next/image';
<Image src={url} alt={alt} width={w} height={h} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw" />

// ✅ For decorative or external images that can't use next/image, add eslint-disable comment
{/* eslint-disable-next-line @next/next/no-img-element */}
<img src={externalUrl} alt="" />
```

