## ESLint Discipline

### Import order

Follow the project's ESLint config (Antfu). The enforced order:

1. Node.js built-ins (`node:fs`, `node:path`)
2. External packages (`lucide-react`, `next-intl`, `@heroui/...`)
3. Internal packages (`@/...`)
4. Parent imports (`../`)
5. Sibling imports (`./`)
6. Type imports (`import type`)

```typescript
// ✅ Correct order
import type { ReactNode } from 'react';
import { ArrowRight, Check, Download } from 'lucide-react';
import { getTranslations } from 'next-intl/server';
import { Fragment } from 'react';
import { SectionHeader } from '@/components/common/SectionHeader';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { Link } from '@/libs/i18n/I18nNavigation';
import type { UserProfile } from '@/types/users';
```

### No unused variables

```typescript
// ❌
const { data, error, isLoading } = useQuery(); // isLoading not used
return <div>{data}</div>;

// ✅ — pick only what you need
const { data } = useQuery();
return <div>{data}</div>;
```

### Tailwind class order

ESLint enforces a specific class ordering (via `eslint-plugin-tailwindcss`). The order roughly follows: positioning → box model → typography → colors → effects → filters.

Use `npx eslint --fix` to auto-fix class ordering.

### No barrel imports from HeroUI

```typescript
// ❌ — pulls entire package, bloats bundle
import { Button, Input, Select } from '@heroui/react';

// ✅ — individual imports
import { Button } from '@heroui/react/button';
import { Input } from '@heroui/react/input';
```

