## Bundle Safety

### No `process.env` in app code

```typescript
// ❌
const apiKey = process.env.API_KEY;

// ✅ — goes through Env.ts validation
import { env } from '@/libs/core/Env';
const apiKey = env.API_KEY; // typed, validated at startup
```

### No large dependencies in client components

Before adding a new npm package:
- Check the bundle size impact (`npm run check:deps` runs Knip)
- Prefer small, tree-shakeable alternatives
- Never import the full lodash (`lodash`) — use `lodash-es` or specific functions

### Dynamic imports for heavy components

```typescript
// ✅ — load heavy modal only when opened
const HeavyModal = dynamic(() => import('./HeavyModal'), { loading: () => <Skeleton /> });

// ✅ — conditional SSR for client-only components
const ClientOnlyChart = dynamic(() => import('./Chart'), { ssr: false });
```
